John de Winburn, deceased, took four oaks in Fullwood within the demesne, value 4d each. The successors of the late constable, Richard de Skelton‚ are responsible for the value and fine, in all 35.

The Prior of Malton took nine waggon-loads of alder in Allantofts within the demesne, value 9²¹, and was let out on bail. He now appears, is convicted, and charged with payment to the Earl of the value and a fine of 9³.

Robert Cave took a green oak in Greathead without the demesne without livery of the foresters or warrant. He is in mercy (3d).

He also felled nine oaks in Scalby Hay without the demesne by night without livery of the foresters or warrant. In mercy (3⁶³).
